WEBVTT

01:40.640 --> 01:45.930
[Speed and Love]

01:46.300 --> 01:48.820
[Episode 22]

02:10.419 --> 02:12.540
The phoenix trees in Nanjing
have a long history

02:12.540 --> 02:13.750
and many stories.

02:14.120 --> 02:15.840
The most accurate account

02:16.260 --> 02:17.350
is that they were planted

02:17.350 --> 02:18.980
for the enshrinement ceremony

02:18.980 --> 02:20.100
of Sun Yat-sen.

02:20.470 --> 02:22.070
But do you know

02:22.470 --> 02:23.980
why they chose phoenix trees?

02:23.980 --> 02:24.610
Why?

02:25.700 --> 02:27.190
Back then, when they were

02:27.190 --> 02:28.440
choosing green plants,

02:28.440 --> 02:30.300
the city planners preferred them

02:30.380 --> 02:31.540
for their shape and shade,

02:31.540 --> 02:33.140
so they planted them

02:33.170 --> 02:34.500
along the main streets.

02:34.710 --> 02:36.440
You know quite a lot about this.

02:37.630 --> 02:38.820
In autumn,

02:39.190 --> 02:41.380
the golden canopy of phoenix trees

02:41.500 --> 02:43.960
stretches across the city
from east to west,

02:44.350 --> 02:45.680
which is very romantic.

02:47.050 --> 02:47.650
Let's go.

03:08.460 --> 03:09.590
Have you settled in?

03:12.960 --> 03:15.290
I rented a place close to the observatory.

03:15.690 --> 03:17.020
The environment is nice

03:17.260 --> 03:18.860
and it's convenient for work.

03:18.860 --> 03:19.990
That's pretty good.

03:20.120 --> 03:21.990
Nanjing is a magical city.

03:22.470 --> 03:23.600
It has a rich history

03:23.660 --> 03:25.660
and a strong sense of everyday life,

03:25.970 --> 03:28.100
always giving a feeling of stability.

03:34.810 --> 03:35.410
By the way,

03:36.060 --> 03:37.790
what kind of coffee do you like?

03:40.660 --> 03:43.100
Vanilla latte with a hint of cinnamon.

03:44.140 --> 03:44.870
What does...

03:45.160 --> 03:46.090
that taste like?

03:47.450 --> 03:48.850
I don't really remember.

03:51.430 --> 03:52.820
What you want to remember

03:52.820 --> 03:54.100
isn't the taste of the coffee,

03:54.100 --> 03:55.700
but the person

03:55.890 --> 03:57.350
you shared it with, right?

04:03.100 --> 04:04.540
What is the guy

04:07.510 --> 04:09.170
who gave you the pen doing now?

04:11.310 --> 04:12.070
I don't know.

04:14.710 --> 04:15.430
Alright.

04:29.140 --> 04:30.510
After we go back to Nanjing,

04:30.510 --> 04:31.700
if you want to run a garage,

04:31.700 --> 04:32.780
I'll do it with you.

04:33.020 --> 04:34.380
If not,

04:34.900 --> 04:36.830
we can open a coffee shop together.

04:39.940 --> 04:41.230
Why a coffee shop?

04:41.820 --> 04:44.630
I just feel it would be nice for us

04:44.630 --> 04:46.360
to open a coffee shop together.

04:46.600 --> 04:49.560
We must choose a location at the foot
of a mountain with phoenix trees.

04:49.560 --> 04:50.800
In autumn,

04:50.820 --> 04:54.080
the golden leaves of phoenix trees
would cover the ground,

04:54.460 --> 04:56.950
and Lightning would run back and forth
over them.

04:56.950 --> 04:58.280
How happy that would be.

05:04.990 --> 05:06.340
Actually, my dream

05:06.950 --> 05:09.350
is to open a small coffee shop
like this one.

05:09.530 --> 05:11.050
I've already thought of a name.

05:11.050 --> 05:12.450
It will be called "Moon."

05:12.580 --> 05:13.870
It has to be on a street

05:13.910 --> 05:15.370
lined with phoenix trees.

05:16.020 --> 05:17.110
In autumn,

05:17.380 --> 05:19.270
when the osmanthus flowers
bloom in Nanjing,

05:19.270 --> 05:22.130
the warm breeze
carries its fragrance everywhere.

05:23.460 --> 05:25.520
People stroll along the long streets

05:25.710 --> 05:27.910
and grab a cup of their favorite coffee.

05:29.140 --> 05:30.070
How delightful.

05:31.670 --> 05:32.510
Sounds nice.

05:33.330 --> 05:36.790
But considering how expensive
storefront rent is in Nanjing,

05:36.820 --> 05:38.680
you'll need to save up quite a bit.

05:38.750 --> 05:40.340
During the years I studied in Canada,

05:40.340 --> 05:41.540
I tutored on weekends

05:41.550 --> 05:43.990
and school breaks.
I've already saved enough.

05:43.990 --> 05:45.220
So does that mean your coffee shop dream

05:45.220 --> 05:46.420
can be realized soon?

05:49.510 --> 05:50.220
Not yet.

05:51.920 --> 05:52.920
Before that,

05:54.060 --> 05:56.060
there's something else I need to do.

06:46.500 --> 06:48.560
Ms. Jiang, I'll be there in 5 minutes.

06:48.680 --> 06:49.580
I'll explain the details

06:49.580 --> 06:51.240
of the old house when I arrive.

06:59.700 --> 07:00.340
Enjoy.

07:00.510 --> 07:01.460
Thank you, sir.

07:09.780 --> 07:10.510
Ms. Jiang,

07:11.220 --> 07:13.510
seriously,
don't make this difficult for me.

07:13.510 --> 07:14.780
That house you're interested in

07:14.780 --> 07:15.870
was sold last year.

07:16.110 --> 07:17.950
I'm really sincere about this.

07:18.020 --> 07:20.070
Could you ask the buyer

07:20.140 --> 07:21.460
if they'd consider reselling it?

07:21.460 --> 07:22.340
I can

07:22.460 --> 07:23.750
offer up to

07:23.750 --> 07:25.140
a 30 percent premium.

07:25.380 --> 07:26.950
My colleagues and I have asked around.

07:26.950 --> 07:27.750
The buyer

07:27.870 --> 07:29.480
is a big businessman from Beijing.

07:29.480 --> 07:31.360
He confirmed the deal

07:31.750 --> 07:33.380
and paid in full the same day.

07:33.790 --> 07:36.920
Do you really think
he'd care about that amount of money?

07:38.330 --> 07:40.420
Please, help me ask again.

07:41.070 --> 07:41.930
If that doesn't work,

07:41.930 --> 07:43.320
arrange a meeting with that buyer.

07:43.320 --> 07:45.250
I'll try to persuade him in person.

07:45.310 --> 07:45.950
Alright.

07:46.670 --> 07:47.710
I'll ask again for you.

07:47.710 --> 07:48.320
Good.

07:48.630 --> 07:49.460
Thank you.

07:49.810 --> 07:50.810
I'll be going now.

08:02.630 --> 08:03.150
Sit.

08:03.460 --> 08:04.310
Good boy.

08:07.580 --> 08:09.380
-You did a great job today.
-Sit.

08:11.390 --> 08:12.150
Let's go.

08:13.620 --> 08:15.550
If Lightning hadn't gone missing,

08:16.410 --> 08:17.870
it would be this big by now.

08:18.470 --> 08:21.430
[Six years ago]

08:28.260 --> 08:28.990
Thanks.

08:31.030 --> 08:32.230
When are you leaving?

08:33.360 --> 08:34.120
The 8th.

08:40.960 --> 08:42.020
By the way, Sanlai,

08:42.150 --> 08:43.240
I've asked.

08:43.299 --> 08:44.960
Lightning's vaccines have expired,

08:44.960 --> 08:46.680
so it probably won't be able
to enter the country with me.

08:46.680 --> 08:48.090
Could you help

08:48.110 --> 08:49.540
have it vaccinated next month

08:49.540 --> 08:50.660
and send it over?

08:50.910 --> 08:52.640
I'll order a pet carrier for it.

08:53.830 --> 08:54.590
Jiang Mu,

08:58.230 --> 08:59.900
I might have some bad news.

09:01.470 --> 09:02.270
What's wrong?

09:03.880 --> 09:05.140
Lightning is missing.

09:06.460 --> 09:07.460
Missing?

09:07.750 --> 09:08.950
How is that possible?

09:10.380 --> 09:11.710
Didn't I tell you before

09:11.960 --> 09:13.910
that Lightning needed to be neutered?

09:13.910 --> 09:14.950
When a dog goes into heat,

09:14.950 --> 09:16.070
it just runs off.

09:16.340 --> 09:17.310
Last night I thought

09:17.310 --> 09:19.070
it'd just run around and come back,

09:19.070 --> 09:21.400
but when I went looking for it,
it was gone.

09:23.080 --> 09:23.800
I'm sorry.

09:24.910 --> 09:26.430
I didn't take good care of Lightning.

09:26.430 --> 09:27.430
But don't worry.

09:27.630 --> 09:29.000
I know how this works.

09:29.460 --> 09:30.320
It was probably

09:30.430 --> 09:32.820
lured away
by some little female dog nearby.

09:32.820 --> 09:33.550
It might even come back

09:33.550 --> 09:34.790
with a girlfriend.

09:35.960 --> 09:36.960
And if it doesn't,

09:38.100 --> 09:40.660
I'll have Xishi give birth
to a better-looking one

09:40.660 --> 09:41.750
and send it to you, okay?

09:41.750 --> 09:42.420
No!

09:42.840 --> 09:44.150
I only want Lightning!

09:45.030 --> 09:46.550
How could it get lost?

09:46.650 --> 09:47.790
I've had it for so long

09:47.790 --> 09:49.150
that I'm attached to it.

09:49.600 --> 09:50.850
I only want Lightning.

09:50.850 --> 09:52.490
We can find it, right?

09:54.140 --> 09:56.380
Why did this have to happen now?

09:58.000 --> 09:59.240
Even Lightning...

10:00.230 --> 10:01.660
is abandoning me?

10:02.740 --> 10:04.000
Don't think like that.

10:04.860 --> 10:05.740
Don't be sad.

10:07.100 --> 10:08.360
It's just a little dog.

10:08.670 --> 10:10.100
Lightning means

10:12.580 --> 10:14.150
more than just a dog to me.

10:23.610 --> 10:24.370
I see.

10:26.880 --> 10:29.680
I'll definitely find Lightning
and bring it back.

10:41.490 --> 10:42.300
Jiang Mu,

10:44.500 --> 10:45.620
if one day

10:46.510 --> 10:48.310
Brandy doesn't want you anymore

10:48.750 --> 10:50.280
and you're unhappy abroad,

10:54.020 --> 10:54.880
then come back.

10:56.720 --> 10:57.750
I'll take you in.

10:59.340 --> 11:00.800
I'll take good care of you.

11:07.010 --> 11:07.980
Jin Zhao...

11:09.810 --> 11:10.810
won't abandon me.

11:54.360 --> 11:56.850
[Purple Mountain Observatory]

12:07.220 --> 12:07.880
Here you go.

12:13.220 --> 12:13.820
Mu.

12:13.980 --> 12:15.480
Take a look at our latest proposal

12:15.480 --> 12:17.410
for the Jupiter satellite system.

13:03.390 --> 13:03.950
Ms. Jiang,

13:03.950 --> 13:05.970
I checked with them 3 times a day

13:05.990 --> 13:07.340
for a whole week.

13:07.620 --> 13:08.340
They said their boss

13:08.340 --> 13:09.740
finally has time to meet.

13:10.200 --> 13:12.050
But they said he's extremely busy

13:12.050 --> 13:12.970
and travels a lot.

13:12.970 --> 13:14.100
And he's only in Nanjing

13:14.100 --> 13:15.550
one day a month.

13:15.690 --> 13:16.950
Then let's do it that day.

13:16.950 --> 13:17.540
Alright.

13:17.860 --> 13:18.990
I'll let you know

13:19.010 --> 13:20.470
as soon as it's confirmed.

13:20.830 --> 13:21.670
Thank you.

13:44.590 --> 13:45.320
Is it...

13:45.900 --> 13:47.530
your dog?

13:47.800 --> 13:49.980
No, it belongs to our coffee shop.

13:50.080 --> 13:52.000
When our boss isn't around,

13:52.130 --> 13:52.980
we staff members

13:52.980 --> 13:54.390
take turns walking it.

13:55.710 --> 13:58.110
It's usually pretty quiet,

13:58.390 --> 13:59.590
but today it's so clingy.

13:59.590 --> 14:00.910
Really different from usual.

14:00.910 --> 14:02.640
Seems like it really likes you.

14:06.840 --> 14:07.510
It...

14:08.740 --> 14:10.670
looks a lot like a dog I used to have.

14:10.790 --> 14:11.920
What a coincidence!

14:18.960 --> 14:20.220
I should get going now.

14:24.630 --> 14:25.230
Jiang Mu,

14:25.640 --> 14:26.640
how have you been?

14:28.450 --> 14:29.180
Pretty good.

14:29.230 --> 14:30.740
I've settled in here.

14:31.020 --> 14:32.120
That's good to hear.

14:32.120 --> 14:33.710
I've been assigned to Beijing

14:33.710 --> 14:35.020
on a long business trip

14:35.280 --> 14:37.540
and probably won't be back anytime soon.

14:38.070 --> 14:39.600
Take care of yourself then.

14:40.100 --> 14:40.790
Thanks.

14:41.790 --> 14:43.050
Actually, I called you

14:43.250 --> 14:46.180
because there's something else
I wanted to tell you.

14:46.500 --> 14:47.190
What is it?

14:47.620 --> 14:48.620
On the day I left,

14:48.730 --> 14:50.660
something interesting happened.

14:50.740 --> 14:51.980
I was taking a taxi to the airport

14:51.980 --> 14:53.890
and passed through
a phoenix tree-lined boulevard.

14:53.890 --> 14:54.890
Guess what I saw?

14:55.430 --> 14:56.150
What?

14:56.430 --> 14:57.580
I saw a coffee shop.

14:58.100 --> 14:59.310
Its name

14:59.420 --> 15:00.620
was actually "Moon."

15:01.240 --> 15:02.840
Someone opened a coffee shop

15:03.390 --> 15:04.750
called Moon
along the phoenix tree-lined boulevard

15:04.750 --> 15:06.410
at the foot of Zijin Mountain.

15:07.000 --> 15:09.100
That person couldn't be you, could it?

15:09.100 --> 15:10.070
How could it be?

15:10.340 --> 15:11.270
Did I ever tell you?

15:11.270 --> 15:12.270
It's just my dream.

15:12.270 --> 15:13.600
It hasn't come true yet.

15:14.590 --> 15:15.720
What a coincidence.

15:16.290 --> 15:17.420
Who could it be then?

15:18.210 --> 15:20.470
They actually made your dream come true.

15:26.500 --> 15:28.110
Where is that coffee shop?

15:28.870 --> 15:30.870
I'll send you the address right now.

15:56.100 --> 15:56.860
Strange.

15:59.160 --> 16:00.610
How did I end up in a park?

16:11.210 --> 16:13.070
What a coincidence. We meet again.

16:13.070 --> 16:13.710
Yes.

16:14.250 --> 16:14.850
Bye.

16:22.530 --> 16:24.080
It belongs to our coffee shop.

16:24.080 --> 16:26.430
It's usually pretty quiet,

16:26.790 --> 16:27.980
but today it's so clingy.

16:27.980 --> 16:29.340
Really different from usual.

16:29.340 --> 16:31.070
Seems like it really likes you.

16:46.960 --> 16:47.840
Lightning?

16:55.020 --> 16:55.900
Lightning!

17:13.680 --> 17:14.480
Lightning!

17:22.319 --> 17:23.630
It really is you!

17:30.110 --> 17:31.440
Where are you taking me?

18:03.910 --> 18:04.680
Doggy?

18:15.170 --> 18:18.100
We must choose a location at the foot
of a mountain with phoenix trees.

18:18.100 --> 18:19.340
In autumn,

18:19.360 --> 18:22.620
the golden leaves of phoenix trees
would cover the ground,

18:22.920 --> 18:25.440
and Lightning would run back and forth
over them.

18:25.440 --> 18:26.770
How happy that would be.

18:30.760 --> 18:31.480
Moon?

18:35.850 --> 18:36.600
Lightning.

18:37.630 --> 18:39.960
Welcome to Moon. What would you like to...

18:41.460 --> 18:43.700
Why is the dog back? Where's Jia?

18:44.800 --> 18:47.000
Quiet, why are you back here on your own?

18:47.430 --> 18:48.470
Quiet?

18:49.690 --> 18:51.550
Did it lead you to the coffee shop?

18:51.950 --> 18:55.080
I can't believe it has learned
how to bring in customers.

18:56.130 --> 18:57.020
The menu is there.

18:57.020 --> 18:58.950
Would you like to order something?

19:06.220 --> 19:07.830
I order delivery from you all the time.

19:07.830 --> 19:09.630
I didn't expect
the shop to be hidden here.

19:09.630 --> 19:11.980
You can't even see the sign
from the entrance.

19:11.980 --> 19:13.370
A lot of customers say that.

19:13.370 --> 19:14.300
Our boss just doesn't want

19:14.300 --> 19:16.430
to cut down the trees in the courtyard.

19:17.500 --> 19:19.460
Your boss is really laid-back.

19:20.060 --> 19:20.660
By the way,

19:20.670 --> 19:23.320
I always order your vanilla latte.

19:23.590 --> 19:25.070
Do you have any other recommendations?

19:23.940 --> 19:28.320
[House Special]

19:26.390 --> 19:28.150
Why don't you try our "Moon?"

19:28.300 --> 19:29.540
It's our bestseller here.

19:29.540 --> 19:30.870
Many customers love it.

19:31.020 --> 19:31.650
Sure.

19:32.100 --> 19:33.930
Alright,
please wait over there for a moment.

19:33.930 --> 19:34.730
Okay, thanks.

19:36.950 --> 19:39.610
Miss,
have you decided what you'd like to drink?

19:40.590 --> 19:41.390
Miss?

19:44.570 --> 19:45.480
This "Moon"

19:45.860 --> 19:47.390
has a really unique design.

19:48.520 --> 19:50.850
That was personally designed by our boss.

19:51.860 --> 19:53.320
So would you like to try it?

19:54.630 --> 19:55.630
I'll have one too.

19:56.110 --> 19:58.370
Alright, please wait over there as well.

21:05.780 --> 21:06.910
Here's your coffee.

21:07.660 --> 21:09.430
This is for our customers to play with.

21:09.430 --> 21:11.090
A child messed it up last time,

21:11.140 --> 21:12.870
and we didn't know how to fix it.

21:13.680 --> 21:15.610
You know how to use a telescope too?

21:16.780 --> 21:18.230
If you want to use it during the day,

21:18.230 --> 21:19.710
you can add a Baader filter.

21:19.710 --> 21:21.880
You might be able to see sunspots.

21:22.610 --> 21:23.540
Okay, thank you.

21:23.620 --> 21:24.750
Here's your coffee.

21:50.400 --> 21:51.330
It really is him.

21:52.380 --> 21:53.380
He's back.

22:10.320 --> 22:12.150
Do you need anything else?

22:13.110 --> 22:15.190
Is Quiet your shop's dog?

22:15.700 --> 22:17.260
No, it's our boss's.

22:17.360 --> 22:19.220
He just keeps the dog at the shop

22:19.220 --> 22:20.820
when he's on business trips.

22:21.440 --> 22:23.490
A coffee shop owner
needs to go on business trips too?

22:23.490 --> 22:25.840
The coffee shop is his side business;
he has a main job.

22:25.840 --> 22:28.160
Actually,
the coffee shop is his main business,

22:28.160 --> 22:29.390
and he has other side ventures.

22:29.390 --> 22:31.360
Is there a difference between the two?

22:31.360 --> 22:32.600
Of course.

22:32.830 --> 22:34.120
Without side ventures,

22:34.120 --> 22:36.920
this shop probably
would have gone under long ago.

22:36.970 --> 22:37.890
Gone under?

22:38.800 --> 22:40.460
Isn't your shop making money?

22:40.540 --> 22:43.390
I heard our business
was really bad a couple of years ago,

22:43.390 --> 22:45.150
but our boss kept the shop alive

22:45.150 --> 22:46.190
through other ventures.

22:46.190 --> 22:47.950
This year,
we've had more returning customers,

22:47.950 --> 22:49.410
so business is doing well.

22:50.070 --> 22:51.070
So where is he now?

22:51.150 --> 22:52.040
On another business trip?

22:52.040 --> 22:54.310
Today I think he went back to school

22:54.340 --> 22:55.740
for his thesis proposal.

22:55.980 --> 22:56.700
School?

22:57.430 --> 22:58.460
Is he very young?

22:58.760 --> 22:59.670
No.

22:59.810 --> 23:01.480
Our boss is in his thirties.

23:01.780 --> 23:04.780
He's just been continuing his studies
at university.

23:06.190 --> 23:07.590
He's quite hardworking.

23:07.950 --> 23:09.640
-Our boss is Superman.
-Our boss is Superman.

23:09.640 --> 23:10.960
He's super busy every day.

23:10.960 --> 23:12.220
And has a lot to handle.

23:14.060 --> 23:15.110
What's his name?

23:15.300 --> 23:16.100
His name is...

23:17.270 --> 23:18.180
How about this?

23:18.460 --> 23:19.350
You can...

23:19.350 --> 23:21.020
talk to us first.

23:21.830 --> 23:23.760
Could you give me his contact info?

23:23.810 --> 23:27.070
I have something very important
to consult with him about.

23:27.300 --> 23:27.910
Alright.

23:28.150 --> 23:29.150
Then please...

23:29.470 --> 23:30.280
register.

23:31.110 --> 23:31.780
Register?

23:32.020 --> 23:34.190
Just write your name, contact info,

23:34.210 --> 23:35.860
and request in it.

23:36.230 --> 23:38.120
Currently you should be...

23:38.310 --> 23:39.040
20th in line.

23:39.380 --> 23:40.110
20th?

23:40.900 --> 23:42.400
What about the 19 people ahead of me?

23:42.400 --> 23:43.500
They're just like you—

23:43.500 --> 23:44.950
women with...

23:45.060 --> 23:46.980
special requests for our boss.

23:53.120 --> 23:54.430
I'm nothing like them.

23:55.220 --> 23:55.950
We know.

23:56.150 --> 23:57.380
Every girl who comes here

23:57.380 --> 23:58.660
says the same thing.

24:00.480 --> 24:01.810
Well, miss.

24:02.070 --> 24:03.260
I'm really sorry.

24:03.420 --> 24:04.670
I can't give you

24:04.670 --> 24:06.070
our boss's contact info.

24:06.300 --> 24:08.110
However, if you register,

24:08.220 --> 24:09.500
I'll report it to him.

24:09.630 --> 24:10.670
If he's interested,

24:10.670 --> 24:12.500
I'm sure he'll reach out to you.

24:13.180 --> 24:14.910
So please register first.

24:34.050 --> 24:34.810
Done.

24:35.490 --> 24:36.620
Alright. Thank you.

25:04.320 --> 25:06.710
The owner of this coffee shop
is pretty handsome,

25:06.710 --> 25:08.700
but he has a rather aloof personality,

25:08.700 --> 25:10.900
giving off a complete "stay away" vibe.

25:12.150 --> 25:13.680
He is indeed very handsome.

25:31.560 --> 25:33.040
Is the owner single?

25:36.770 --> 25:38.640
When chatting with the staff,

25:38.910 --> 25:40.190
I heard he's married,

25:40.330 --> 25:42.860
and his wife and children
are settled abroad.

25:43.470 --> 25:44.520
He's married?

25:55.540 --> 25:58.630
[Purple Mountain Observatory]

25:59.020 --> 26:01.140
Alright, then let's go with this plan.

26:01.140 --> 26:03.140
I'll talk to the director on Monday.

26:03.780 --> 26:05.370
What are you planning to do this weekend?

26:05.370 --> 26:07.150
I'm going shopping for some clothes

26:07.150 --> 26:08.800
and maybe having afternoon tea.

26:08.800 --> 26:09.530
Sounds good.

26:11.420 --> 26:13.620
It's been a week. Why hasn't he replied?

26:23.320 --> 26:24.320
You finally came.

26:24.540 --> 26:26.070
You lost something, right?

26:26.520 --> 26:28.280
A pen. Have you seen it?

26:28.630 --> 26:30.740
Yes. It was originally in the pen holder.

26:30.740 --> 26:33.040
I thought you'd come back
for it the next day.

26:33.040 --> 26:34.410
I've been busy with work,

26:34.410 --> 26:35.730
so I only came today.

26:36.000 --> 26:36.980
Well, I have to tell you this.

26:36.980 --> 26:39.380
I'm sorry
you came all this way for nothing.

26:39.500 --> 26:41.970
Your pen was taken by our boss
a couple of days ago.

26:41.970 --> 26:43.740
But if you're free

26:43.740 --> 26:45.460
Sunday morning, you can come here

26:45.460 --> 26:46.150
and he'll

26:46.410 --> 26:48.010
personally return it to you.

26:48.690 --> 26:49.360
Thank you.

26:49.960 --> 26:51.430
Please tell your boss

26:51.640 --> 26:53.240
I'll see him Sunday morning.

26:53.400 --> 26:54.010
Okay.

27:17.970 --> 27:21.330
♪ What was it that brought me to you? ♪

27:21.720 --> 27:23.630
♪ Perhaps it was fate's design ♪

27:24.200 --> 27:27.940
♪ Through all our winding paths,
we always find each other ♪

27:27.960 --> 27:31.560
♪ The storm turned to rain,
and everything was swept away ♪

27:31.590 --> 27:33.300
♪ Slowly, everything becomes clear ♪

27:33.320 --> 27:35.680
♪ In your gaze ♪

27:35.970 --> 27:37.930
♪ I found the answer ♪

27:37.960 --> 27:40.000
♪ There's a feeling so strong ♪

27:38.390 --> 27:40.030
Ms. Jiang, the buyer has agreed to meet.

27:40.030 --> 27:43.160
♪ Our story is still unfolding ♪

27:40.190 --> 27:41.300
This Sunday,

27:41.380 --> 27:42.980
he'll be in Nanjing for a day.

27:43.060 --> 27:44.020
Does this time work for you?

27:43.300 --> 27:47.210
♪ Waiting for the perfect ending ♪

27:44.110 --> 27:45.070
Of course.

27:45.350 --> 27:47.140
Please send me the time and location.

27:47.140 --> 27:47.800
Sure thing.

27:48.920 --> 27:51.370
♪ It all began the moment I met you ♪

27:51.390 --> 27:53.860
♪ There's a pull I cannot explain ♪

27:53.890 --> 27:57.010
♪ My eyes follow you,
my heart chases after you ♪

27:56.220 --> 27:58.350
Jiang Mu,
come to the office tomorrow morning.

27:57.030 --> 27:58.840
♪ I just can't help it ♪

27:58.540 --> 28:00.390
Our team is going on a business trip
to Beijing next Monday,

27:58.860 --> 28:01.310
♪ When I gaze across the sky ♪

28:00.590 --> 28:02.390
so we need to have a meeting
before the trip

28:01.340 --> 28:03.840
♪ Not even miles can keep us apart ♪

28:02.440 --> 28:03.890
to discuss the content and arrangements.

28:03.860 --> 28:06.870
♪ Sweet longing drifts on the wind ♪

28:04.110 --> 28:05.020
Okay.

28:06.890 --> 28:09.110
♪ I can feel you near ♪

28:09.470 --> 28:11.900
♪ Feel you're with me ♪

28:11.920 --> 28:14.220
♪ Forget the sunsets, forget the tides ♪

28:14.400 --> 28:16.460
♪ Watch the years pass
and wander the world ♪

28:14.430 --> 28:16.260
I'll be at the office at 8:30.

28:16.810 --> 28:18.490
♪ You're the only one in my heart ♪

28:17.060 --> 28:18.220
After it's over,

28:18.300 --> 28:20.020
I'll go to the coffee shop at 9:30.

28:18.510 --> 28:21.180
♪ It all began the moment I met you ♪

28:20.700 --> 28:21.740
I should make it in time, right?

28:21.210 --> 28:23.340
♪ The road ahead ♪

28:23.600 --> 28:25.600
♪ And every step we take ♪

28:25.620 --> 28:28.240
♪ Guide us toward happiness ♪

28:26.260 --> 28:27.910
Everyone,
take a look at the paper by the professor

28:27.910 --> 28:30.190
from USTC that I just mentioned.

28:28.530 --> 28:31.690
♪ It's all to see you ♪

28:30.630 --> 28:32.740
We'll all be going on a business trip
to Beijing next Monday.

28:32.740 --> 28:33.670
Don't be late.

28:33.910 --> 28:34.870
If you have any questions,

28:34.870 --> 28:36.300
take a look now

28:36.320 --> 28:37.250
and discuss them

28:37.430 --> 28:39.390
so it'll be easier
to bring them up by then.

28:39.390 --> 28:40.020
Alright?

28:40.220 --> 28:41.550
Zhou, come here.

28:50.040 --> 28:52.570
Hi, I'm the one
who's coming to pick up the pen.

28:52.900 --> 28:54.740
Something came up at work,
so I might be a little late.

28:54.740 --> 28:56.140
Is your boss still there?

28:56.510 --> 28:57.710
Please wait a moment.

28:59.850 --> 29:00.530
Hello.

29:00.800 --> 29:01.840
Our boss said

29:02.060 --> 29:04.220
to take your time
and be careful on the way.

29:04.220 --> 29:05.320
He'll be waiting here for you

29:05.320 --> 29:06.580
and won't go anywhere.

29:08.220 --> 29:08.950
Okay.

30:35.030 --> 30:35.870
You're here.

30:38.590 --> 30:39.460
Where is he?

30:40.430 --> 30:41.830
Wasn't he waiting for me?

30:42.500 --> 30:43.430
He's over there.

31:14.230 --> 31:20.630
♪ Perhaps the weather's damp and mild ♪

31:20.650 --> 31:24.480
♪ Perhaps it's about the habit
of bearing ♪

31:25.190 --> 31:28.480
♪ A certain bitter emotion ♪

31:28.500 --> 31:34.570
♪ For you, it's all too easy ♪

31:35.520 --> 31:41.230
♪ To be happy or heartbroken,
as transparent as I can be ♪

31:42.220 --> 31:48.130
♪ Crossing the line for love,
I've walked 10,000 kilometers ♪

31:49.470 --> 31:55.630
♪ Brave enough to be sure is my instinct ♪

31:55.780 --> 31:56.940
♪ I believe ♪

31:56.960 --> 32:01.130
♪ Maybe it just takes a little resolve ♪

32:01.390 --> 32:04.620
♪ To turn wishes into shooting stars ♪

32:05.200 --> 32:10.230
♪ Mirroring the eyes that gaze at me ♪

32:24.010 --> 32:29.830
♪ The crash of waves comes and goes ♪

32:30.850 --> 32:34.330
♪ After leaning on you and hesitating ♪

32:34.550 --> 32:37.830
♪ I've never been so steadfast and true ♪

32:37.990 --> 32:43.830
♪ My love needs to stay clear-eyed ♪

32:44.880 --> 32:50.830
♪ After the scorching ache,
I still reach for a sincere heart ♪

32:52.180 --> 32:58.080
♪ Crossing the line for love,
I've walked 10,000 kilometers ♪

32:59.440 --> 33:05.580
♪ Brave enough to be sure is my instinct ♪

33:05.600 --> 33:10.710
♪ I believe
maybe it just takes a little resolve ♪

33:10.990 --> 33:14.330
♪ To turn wishes into shooting stars ♪

33:14.940 --> 33:19.330
♪ Mirroring the eyes that gaze at me ♪

33:19.350 --> 33:24.440
♪ Fearless as a moth
darting into the fire ♪

33:24.470 --> 33:32.530
♪ I'd rewrite the endings
of missed chances a thousand times ♪

33:33.620 --> 33:39.170
♪ Crossing the line for love,
I've walked 10,000 kilometers ♪

33:35.870 --> 33:37.110
It really is you.

33:40.770 --> 33:46.670
♪ Brave enough to be sure is my instinct ♪

33:40.980 --> 33:42.110
Who else could it be?

33:46.680 --> 33:47.890
♪ I believe ♪

33:47.540 --> 33:48.500
S-Sit.

33:48.080 --> 33:51.930
♪ Maybe it just takes a little resolve ♪

33:51.950 --> 33:55.870
♪ To turn wishes into shooting stars ♪

33:56.070 --> 34:01.110
♪ Mirroring the eyes that gaze at me ♪

34:06.860 --> 34:13.679
♪ Crossing the path,
stepping into your life ♪

34:10.280 --> 34:12.540
Did you guess it was me
because of the pen?

34:12.659 --> 34:14.520
There aren't many people who know

34:14.580 --> 34:15.830
how to use a telescope,

34:15.830 --> 34:17.020
make Lightning act strangely,

34:17.020 --> 34:17.949
and own this pen.

34:24.389 --> 34:25.719
You went back to school?

34:26.659 --> 34:27.920
Just getting a degree.

34:41.600 --> 34:43.600
Strawberry flavor. Your favorite.

34:48.159 --> 34:49.389
I don't like it now.

34:51.699 --> 34:53.560
Then I'll get you a different one.

34:59.550 --> 35:00.510
But I'm hungry.

35:18.980 --> 35:20.440
Why didn't you contact me?

35:21.660 --> 35:22.740
Being so far apart,

35:25.390 --> 35:27.520
it's always hard to keep things going.

35:28.980 --> 35:31.040
If you meet someone suitable nearby,

35:31.750 --> 35:34.060
it would put everyone
in an awkward position.

35:34.060 --> 35:35.700
It's better to live a little more easily.

35:35.700 --> 35:37.100
So are you living easily?

35:42.740 --> 35:44.010
Are you married?

35:50.510 --> 35:51.370
What about you?

35:52.950 --> 35:54.280
Do you have a boyfriend?

35:55.700 --> 35:56.330
Yes.

35:58.740 --> 36:01.140
We're getting married
at the end of the year.

36:01.140 --> 36:02.260
I came to Nanjing

36:02.570 --> 36:03.610
for him.

36:12.050 --> 36:12.860
That's good.

36:20.560 --> 36:22.690
If I invite you to my wedding,

36:23.130 --> 36:24.000
will you come?

36:27.970 --> 36:30.100
I'm not sure if I'll be in Nanjing then.

36:30.470 --> 36:32.530
I'll let you know the date in advance.

36:35.240 --> 36:35.950
I'll try.

36:41.840 --> 36:44.040
I need to go somewhere else later, so...

37:17.080 --> 37:18.540
Give me your phone number.

37:18.900 --> 37:20.160
Without contact info,

37:20.180 --> 37:22.240
how am I supposed to tell you the date?

37:24.970 --> 37:25.770
What's wrong?

37:26.540 --> 37:27.740
Don't want to chip in?

37:44.000 --> 37:45.000
Are you the one

37:46.390 --> 37:47.850
who bought that old house?

37:53.350 --> 37:54.120
Yes.

37:57.280 --> 37:57.990
I knew it.

37:58.410 --> 37:59.210
Tomorrow....

37:59.390 --> 38:00.120
Tomorrow...

38:03.320 --> 38:05.450
I'm going on a business trip tomorrow.

38:05.470 --> 38:06.600
When I get back,

38:07.370 --> 38:09.700
we'll have a proper talk about Lightning.

38:32.290 --> 38:35.390
♪ I leave after your curtain call ♪

38:38.100 --> 38:41.290
♪ I ask the tired bird ♪

38:42.080 --> 38:45.140
♪ About your news ♪

38:47.400 --> 38:51.050
♪ You're too serious in
both your passion and silence ♪

38:53.370 --> 38:58.550
♪ That's why you're always
covered in scars ♪

39:00.200 --> 39:03.800
♪ If darkness can stop the pain ♪

39:04.110 --> 39:09.300
♪ I'll let you sleep a bit longer ♪

39:10.790 --> 39:14.800
♪ I'll stay by your side tonight ♪

39:17.680 --> 39:22.800
♪ I want to meet the dusk with you ♪

39:23.160 --> 39:27.040
♪ Then stay with me until dawn ♪

39:25.210 --> 39:26.040
Jin Zhao,

39:27.150 --> 39:28.500
you're finally back.

39:27.820 --> 39:33.860
♪ Our moment together
feels like a lifetime ♪

39:30.100 --> 39:32.500
I've been looking for you
for so many years.

39:32.810 --> 39:34.690
Why are you only showing up now?

39:34.310 --> 39:37.960
♪ Your remaining warmth before dawn ♪

39:36.270 --> 39:37.270
Why?

39:38.440 --> 39:42.550
♪ Is enough for me to sink in soberly ♪

39:39.280 --> 39:40.360
Why?

39:42.890 --> 39:47.050
♪ But I'm still waiting
for every dawn and dusk ♪

39:47.080 --> 39:51.010
♪ To run towards you again ♪

39:51.040 --> 39:58.550
♪ Even if I hug you for a moment ♪

39:58.550 --> 39:59.320
Yes.

40:01.620 --> 40:04.060
We're getting married
at the end of the year.

40:04.060 --> 40:05.350
I came to Nanjing

40:05.420 --> 40:06.540
for him.

40:13.600 --> 40:17.840
♪ Meet the dusk with you ♪

40:18.330 --> 40:22.090
♪ Then stay with me until dawn ♪

40:22.740 --> 40:27.810
♪ Our moment together
feels like a lifetime ♪

40:29.450 --> 40:33.090
♪ Your remaining warmth before dawn ♪

40:33.200 --> 40:37.590
♪ Is enough for me to sink in soberly ♪

40:37.660 --> 40:39.660
♪ But I'm still waiting ♪

40:39.940 --> 40:41.590
♪ For every dawn and dusk ♪

40:41.610 --> 40:45.540
♪ To run towards you again ♪

40:45.920 --> 40:49.590
♪ Until I can embrace you ♪

40:51.800 --> 40:55.090
♪ For a lifetime ♪
